<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900503-0145</DOCNO><DOCID>900503-0145.</DOCID><HL>   Grow Group Settles   Felony, Misdemeanor   Charges From Fire</HL><DATE>05/03/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   GRO</CO><LP>   NEW YORK -- Grow Group Inc. said the company and two ofits executives settled charges stemming from a 1988 chemicalfire at its Commerce, Calif., facility.   The fire released a cloud of chlorine gas over thecompany's warehouse, forcing authorities to evacuate some25,000 residents in surrounding neighborhoods.</LP><TEXT>   The company said it would incur a $3.8 million charge inits fiscal third quarter ended March 31 because of thesettlement and other related matters concerning its consumerand professional products group. Grow Group reported a lossof $2,263,000 in the March 1989 quarter.   Under terms of the settlement, the company said it pleadedno contest to one felony and three misdemeanor charges ofviolations of the California Hazardous Waste Control Act,agreeing to pay a fine of $400,000.   The company also agreed to contribute $350,000 to fundacademic scholarships at five high schools in the Commercearea as restitution for the costs incurred by Los AngelesCounty agencies and municipalities.   Grow Group also agreed to be placed on summary probationfor three years.   Two executives in the company's consumer and professionalproducts group pleaded &quot;no contest&quot; to four misdemeanorcharges.   The company said it has reached an agreement in principleto settle a related civil action which the California stateattorney general had been considering bringing against thecompany.</TEXT></DOC>